Interface GTNetInstrumentSecurityJpaRepository

All Superinterfaces:
org.springframework.data.repository.CrudRepository<GTNetInstrumentSecurity,Integer>, GTNetInstrumentSecurityJpaRepositoryCustom, org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository<GTNetInstrumentSecurity,Integer>, org.springframework.data.repository.ListCrudRepository<GTNetInstrumentSecurity,Integer>, org.springframework.data.repository.ListPagingAndSortingRepository<GTNetInstrumentSecurity,Integer>, org.springframework.data.repository.PagingAndSortingRepository<GTNetInstrumentSecurity,Integer>, org.springframework.data.repository.query.QueryByExampleExecutor<GTNetInstrumentSecurity>, org.springframework.data.repository.Repository<GTNetInstrumentSecurity,Integer>
public interface GTNetInstrumentSecurityJpaRepository extends org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository<GTNetInstrumentSecurity,Integer>, GTNetInstrumentSecurityJpaRepositoryCustom
Repository for GTNetInstrumentSecurity entities. Provides access to security instruments in the GTNet instrument pool, identified by ISIN and currency. For price data operations, use this repository to find instruments and then query GTNetLastpriceJpaRepository for the associated price data.

  • Method Details

    • findByIsinAndCurrency

      Optional<GTNetInstrumentSecurity> findByIsinAndCurrency(String isin, String currency)
      Finds a security instrument by its ISIN and currency.
      Parameters:
      isin - the ISIN code (ISO 6166)
      currency - the currency code (ISO 4217)
      Returns:
      the instrument if found

    • findLocalInstruments

      @Query(nativeQuery=true, value="SELECT g.* FROM gt_net_instrument_security g\nJOIN security s ON g.isin = s.isin AND g.currency = s.currency") List<GTNetInstrumentSecurity> findLocalInstruments()
      Finds all local security instruments (those that exist in the local database). Uses a JOIN to determine locality dynamically based on matching ISIN and currency.
      Returns:
      list of local security instruments

    • findForeignInstruments

      @Query(nativeQuery=true, value="SELECT g.* FROM gt_net_instrument_security g\nLEFT JOIN security s ON g.isin = s.isin AND g.currency = s.currency\nWHERE s.id_securitycurrency IS NULL") List<GTNetInstrumentSecurity> findForeignInstruments()
      Finds all foreign security instruments (those that do NOT exist in the local database). Uses a LEFT JOIN to find instruments with no matching local security.
      Returns:
      list of foreign security instruments

    • findByIsinCurrencyKeys

      @Query("SELECT s FROM GTNetInstrumentSecurity s WHERE CONCAT(s.isin, \'|\', s.currency) IN :keys") List<GTNetInstrumentSecurity> findByIsinCurrencyKeys(@Param("keys") List<String> keys)
      Finds security instruments by a list of composite keys (ISIN|currency format). Used for batch lookups when matching instruments from GTNet requests.
      Parameters:
      keys - list of composite keys in "ISIN|currency" format
      Returns:
      list of matching security instruments

    • findLocalSecurityMappings

      @Query(nativeQuery=true, value="SELECT g.id_gt_net_instrument, s.id_securitycurrency\nFROM gt_net_instrument_security g\nJOIN security s ON g.isin = s.isin AND g.currency = s.currency\nWHERE g.id_gt_net_instrument IN (:ids)") List<Object[]> findLocalSecurityMappings(@Param("ids") List<Integer> instrumentIds)
      Determines which GTNet security instruments have matching local securities via JOIN. Returns mapping from GTNet instrument ID to local security ID. Uses a native JOIN query to find local securities that match the ISIN and currency of the given GTNet instruments. This allows dynamic determination of instrument locality without storing the reference in the GTNetInstrument entity.
      Parameters:
      instrumentIds - list of GTNet instrument IDs to check for locality
      Returns:
      list of Object[] where [0] = idGtNetInstrument (Integer), [1] = idSecuritycurrency (Integer)
